task.summary: adding a custom user manager to handle the creation of the custom user model that will be added later.

Created database tables and schema for the residencehalls application and the remainder of the accounts application. This includes Resident Assistants, Students, Hall Directors, Residence Halls, Suites, Hallways, and Rooms. Some of these might not be used in the future, but they are here just in case.
Connected the new user model to the settings file for authentication. Added the templates and static folders to each app and the overall project.
did some code refactoring and updated the logout redirect url
fixed some authentication bugs with the forms cleaned_data. Added a custom template filter to better display the forms errors.
added the functionality to allow reslife to submit the room assignment of residents.
did some submission security js to the tracker room assignment field
updated tracker elements to simply get dumped json data back from the django views. Rather than updating the entire DOM, I am now just updating the current value, but still saving the data correctly.
did some template updates within the student information card application
